quran[75]{c,v,t}:
  8,1,"They ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ regarding the spoils of war. Say, ‚ÄúTheir distribution is decided by God and His Messenger. So be mindful of God, settle your affairs, and obey God and His Messenger if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers.‚ÄĚ"
  8,2,"The ňĻtrueňļ believers are only those whose hearts tremble at the remembrance of God, whose faith increases when His revelations are recited to them, and who put their trust in their Lord"
  8,3,ňĻThey areňļ those who establish prayer and donate from what We have provided for them
  8,4,"It is they who are the true believers. They will have elevated ranks, forgiveness, and an honourable provision from their Lord"
  8,5,"Similarly, when your Lord brought you ňĻO Prophetňļ out of your home for a just cause, a group of believers was totally against it"
  8,6,"They disputed with you about the truth after it had been made clear, as if they were being driven to death with their eyes wide open"
  8,7,"ňĻRemember, O believers,ňļ when God promised ňĻto giveňļ you the upper hand over either target, you wished to capture the unarmed party.¬†But it was God‚Äôs Will¬†to establish the truth by His Words and uproot the disbelievers"
  8,8,to firmly establish the truth and wipe out falsehood‚ÄĒeven to the dismay of the wicked
  8,9,"ňĻRememberňļ when you cried out to your Lord for help, He answered, ‚ÄúI will reinforce you with a thousand angels‚ÄĒfollowed by many others.‚ÄĚ"
  8,10,"And God made this a sign of victory and reassurance to your hearts. Victory comes only from God. Surely God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,11,"ňĻRememberňļ when He caused drowsiness to overcome you, giving you serenity.¬†And He sent down rain from the sky to purify you, free you from Satan‚Äôs whispers, strengthen your hearts, and make ňĻyourňļ steps firm"
  8,12,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when your Lord revealed to the angels, ‚ÄúI am with you. So make the believers stand firm. I will cast horror into the hearts of the disbelievers. So strike their necks and strike their fingertips.‚ÄĚ"
  8,13,"This is because they defied God and His Messenger. And whoever defies God and His Messenger, then ňĻknow thatňļ God is surely severe in punishment"
  8,14,"That ňĻworldly punishmentňļ is yours, so taste it! Then the disbelievers will suffer the torment of the Fire"
  8,15,"O believers! When you face the disbelievers in battle, never turn your backs to them"
  8,16,"And whoever does so on such an occasion‚ÄĒunless it is a manoeuvre or to join their own troops‚ÄĒwill earn the displeasure of God, and their home will be Hell. What an evil destination"
  8,17,"It was not you ňĻbelieversňļ who killed them, but it was God Who did so. Nor was it you ňĻO Prophetňļ who threw ňĻa handful of sand at the disbelieversňļ,¬†but it was God Who did so, rendering the believers a great favour. Surely God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,18,"As such, God frustrates the evil plans of the disbelievers"
  8,19,"If you ňĻMeccansňļ sought judgment, now it has come to you. And if you cease, it will be for your own good. But if you persist, We will persist. And your forces‚ÄĒno matter how numerous they might be‚ÄĒwill not benefit you whatsoever. For God is certainly with the believers"
  8,20,O believers! Obey God and His Messenger and do not turn away from him while you hear ňĻhis callňļ
  8,21,"Do not be like those who say, ‚ÄúWe hear,‚ÄĚ but in fact they are not listening"
  8,22,"Indeed, the worst of all beings in the sight of God are the ňĻwilfullyňļ deaf and dumb, who do not understand"
  8,23,"Had God known any goodness in them, He would have certainly made them hear. ňĻButňļ even if He had made them hear, they would have surely turned away heedlessly"
  8,24,"O believers! Respond to God and His Messenger when he calls you to that which gives you life. And know that God stands between a person and their heart, and that to Him you will all be gathered"
  8,25,Beware of a trial that will not only affect the wrongdoers among you. And know that God is severe in punishment
  8,26,"Remember when you had been vastly outnumbered and oppressed in the land,¬†constantly in fear of attacks by your enemy, then He sheltered you, strengthened you with His help, and provided you with good things so perhaps you would be thankful"
  8,27,"O believers! Do not betray God and the Messenger, nor betray your trusts knowingly"
  8,28,And know that your wealth and your children are only a test and that with God is a great reward
  8,29,"O believers! If you are mindful of God, He will grant you a standard ňĻto distinguish between right and wrongňļ, absolve you of your sins, and forgive you. And God is the Lord of infinite bounty"
  8,30,"And ňĻremember, O Prophet,ňļ when the disbelievers conspired to capture, kill, or exile you. They planned, but God also planned. And God is the best of planners"
  8,31,"Whenever Our revelations are recited to them, they challenge ňĻyouňļ, ‚ÄúWe have already heard ňĻthe recitationňļ. If we wanted, we could have easily produced something similar. This ňĻQuranňļ is nothing but ancient fables!‚ÄĚ"
  8,32,"And ňĻrememberňļ when they prayed, ‚ÄúO God! If this is indeed the truth from You, then rain down stones upon us from the sky or overcome us with a painful punishment.‚ÄĚ"
  8,33,But God would never punish them while you ňĻO Prophetňļ were in their midst. Nor would He ever punish them if they prayed for forgiveness
  8,34,"And why should God not punish them while they hinder pilgrims from the Sacred Mosque, claiming to be its rightful guardians? None has the right to guardianship except those mindful ňĻof Godňļ, but most pagans do not know"
  8,35,Their prayer at the Sacred House was nothing but whistling and clapping. So taste the punishment for your disbelief
  8,36,Surely the disbelievers spend their wealth to hinder others from the Path of God. They will continue to spend to the point of regret. Then they will be defeated and the disbelievers will be driven into Hell
  8,37,so God may separate the evil from the good. He will pile up the evil ones all together and then cast them into Hell. They are the ňĻtrueňļ losers
  8,38,"Tell the disbelievers that if they desist, their past will be forgiven. But if they persist, then they have an example in those destroyed before them"
  8,39,"Fight against them until there is no more persecution‚ÄĒand ňĻyourňļ devotion will be entirely to God. But if they desist, then surely God is All-Seeing of what they do"
  8,40,"And if they do not comply, then know that God is your Protector. What an excellent Protector, and what an excellent Helper"
  8,41,"Know that whatever spoils you take, one-fifth is for God and the Messenger, his close relatives, orphans, the poor, and ňĻneedyňļ travellers, if you ňĻtrulyňļ believe in God and what We revealed to Our servant on that decisive day when the two armies met ňĻat Badrňļ. And God is Most Capable of everything"
  8,42,"ňĻRememberňļ when you were on the near side of the valley, your enemy on the far side, and the caravan was below you. Even if the two armies had made an appointment ňĻto meetňļ, both would have certainly missed it.¬†Still it transpired so God may establish what He had destined‚ÄĒthat those who were to perish and those who were to survive might do so after the truth had been made clear to both. Surely God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,43,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when God showed them in your dream as few in number. Had He shown them to you as many, you ňĻbelieversňļ would have certainly faltered and disputed in the matter. But God spared you ňĻfrom thatňļ. Surely He knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  8,44,"Then when your armies met, God made them appear as few in your eyes, and made you appear as few in theirs, so God may establish what He had destined. And to God ňĻallňļ matters will be returned ňĻfor judgmentňļ"
  8,45,"O believers! When you face an enemy, stand firm and remember God often so you may triumph"
  8,46,"Obey God and His Messenger and do not dispute with one another, or you would be discouraged and weakened. Persevere! Surely God is with those who persevere"
  8,47,"Do not be like those ňĻpagansňļ who left their homes arrogantly, only to be seen by people and to hinder others from God‚Äôs Path. And God is Fully Aware of what they do"
  8,48,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Satan made their ňĻevilňļ deeds appealing to them, and said, ‚ÄúNo one can overcome you today. I am surely by your side.‚ÄĚ But when the two forces faced off, he cowered and said, ‚ÄúI have absolutely nothing to do with you. I certainly see what you do not see. I truly fear God, for God is severe in punishment.‚ÄĚ"
  8,49,"ňĻRememberňļ when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, ‚ÄúThese ňĻbelieversňļ are deluded by their faith.‚ÄĚ But whoever puts their trust in God, surely God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,50,"If only you could see when the angels take the souls of the disbelievers, beating their faces and backs, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúTaste the torment of burning"
  8,51,This is ňĻthe rewardňļ for what your hands have done. And God is never unjust to ňĻHisňļ creation.‚ÄĚ
  8,52,"Their fate is that of the people of Pharaoh and those before them‚ÄĒthey all disbelieved in God‚Äôs signs, so God seized them for their sins. Indeed, God is All-Powerful, severe in punishment"
  8,53,"This is because God would never discontinue His favour to a people until they discontinue their faith. Surely God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,54,"That was the case with Pharaoh‚Äôs people and those before them‚ÄĒthey all rejected the signs of their Lord, so We destroyed them for their sins and drowned Pharaoh‚Äôs people. They were all wrongdoers"
  8,55,"Indeed, the worst of all beings in the sight of God are those who persist in disbelief, never to have faith‚ÄĒ"
  8,56,"ňĻnamelyňļ those with whom you ňĻO Prophetňļ have entered into treaties, but they violate them every time, not fearing the consequences"
  8,57,"If you ever encounter them in battle, make a fearsome example of them, so perhaps those who would follow them may be deterred"
  8,58,"And if you ňĻO Prophetňļ see signs of betrayal by a people, respond by openly terminating your treaty with them. Surely God does not like those who betray"
  8,59,Do not let those disbelievers¬†think they are not within reach. They will have no escape
  8,60,Prepare against them what you ňĻbelieversňļ can of ňĻmilitaryňļ power and cavalry to deter God‚Äôs enemies and your enemies as well as other enemies unknown to you but known to God. Whatever you spend in the cause of God will be paid to you in full and you will not be wronged
  8,61,"If the enemy is inclined towards peace, make peace with them. And put your trust in God. Indeed, He ňĻaloneňļ is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,62,"But if their intention is only to deceive you, then God is certainly sufficient for you. He is the One Who has supported you with His help and with the believers"
  8,63,"He brought their hearts together. Had you spent all the riches in the earth, you could not have united their hearts. But God has united them. Indeed, He is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,64,O Prophet! God is sufficient for you and for the believers who follow you
  8,65,"O Prophet! Motivate the believers to fight. If there are twenty steadfast among you, they will overcome two hundred. And if there are one hundred of you, they will overcome one thousand of the disbelievers, for they are a people who do not comprehend"
  8,66,"Now God has lightened your burden, for He knows that there is weakness in you. So if there are a hundred steadfast among you, they will overcome two hundred. And if there be one thousand, they will overcome two thousand, by God‚Äôs Will. And God is with the steadfast"
  8,67,"It is not fit for a prophet that he should take captives until he has thoroughly subdued the land. You ňĻbelieversňļ settled with the fleeting gains of this world,¬†while God‚Äôs aim ňĻfor youňļ is the Hereafter. God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,68,"Had it not been for a prior decree from God,¬†you would have certainly been disciplined with a tremendous punishment for whatever ňĻransomňļ you have taken"
  8,69,"Now enjoy what you have taken, for it is lawful and good. And be mindful of God. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  8,70,"O Prophet! Tell the captives in your custody, ‚ÄúIf God finds goodness in your hearts, He will give you better than what has been taken from you, and forgive you. For God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  8,71,"But if their intention is only to betray you ňĻO Prophetňļ, they sought to betray God before. But He gave you power over them. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  8,72,"Those who believed, emigrated, and strived with their wealth and lives in the cause of God, as well as those who gave them shelter and help‚ÄĒthey are truly guardians of one another. As for those who believed but did not emigrate, you have no obligations to them until they emigrate. But if they seek your help ňĻagainst persecutionňļ in faith, it is your obligation to help them, except against people bound with you in a treaty. God is All-Seeing of what you do"
  8,73,"As for the disbelievers, they are guardians of one another. And unless you ňĻbelieversňļ act likewise, there will be great oppression and corruption in the land"
  8,74,"Those who believed, migrated, and struggled in the cause of God, and those who gave ňĻthemňļ shelter and help, they are the true believers. They will have forgiveness and an honourable provision"
  8,75,"And those who later believed, migrated, and struggled alongside you, they are also with you. But only blood relatives are now entitled to inherit from one another,¬†as ordained by God. Surely God has ňĻfullňļ knowledge of everything"